Reasoning: The paper deals with developing a new metric for quantifying end-to-end throughput in multihop wireless networks, which falls under the domain of network communication and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization and mathematical analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Additionally, the paper discusses the interference model and the scaling law, which could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.PE (Performance).
